board
Homonym Number:  1
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a shearing floor, a killing floor of a freezing works;  the area in a woolshed used for shearing on; or the working floor of a freezing works; occas. the complement of shearers at work, cf all aboard, clear the board, shearing board (usu. constr. with the, and sometimes pl the boards).


