Date:  26/2/1965
Source:  Listener (New Zealand Listener)
Author:
Vol / Page:  15
Edition:
Quote:   <i>Board</i>: The area in a woolshed used for shearing. In some 16-stand sheds there are two boards, each with its ringer. At Masterton there is a six-stand board with catching and counting-out pens behind, extending for over 50 feet across the front of the stadium.
Notes:   (H.A.L. Laing)

